The following pseudocode detection rules are designed for integration into SIEM/SOAR platforms (Sigma-compatible format). Adapt field names to your environment.

**Detection 1: FortiGate Branded Password Authentication**

```
title: TheGentlemen FortiGate Branded VPN Password
status: experimental
logsource:
  product: fortinet
  service: sslvpn
detection:
  selection:
    user: 'root'
    action: 'tunnel-up'
  condition: selection
  # Cross-reference with known passwords: gentlemen25, Gentlemen25, gentle26
  # FortiGate logs may not capture plaintext passwords —
  # alert on any 'root' SSL VPN tunnel-up event as anomalous
level: high
```

**Detection 2: Pre-Encryption Service Termination Pattern**

```
title: TheGentlemen Pre-Encryption Service Kill Chain
status: experimental
logsource:
  product: linux
  category: process_creation
detection:
  docker_stop:
    CommandLine|contains: 'docker stop'
  qemu_kill:
    CommandLine|contains|any:
      - 'pkill -9 qemu'
      - 'pkill -9 -f qemu-system'
  mysql_stop:
    CommandLine|contains|any:
      - 'systemctl stop mysql'
      - 'systemctl stop mariadb'
  condition: docker_stop or qemu_kill or mysql_stop
  # High confidence when 2+ of these fire within 60 seconds on the same host
level: critical
```

**Detection 3: G-BOT C2 Beacon Indicators**

```
title: TheGentlemen G-BOT C2 PID File and SOCKS Port
